Minor nitpick, Hastur, Chaugnar Faugn, and Tsathoggua were made by Robert W. Chambers, Frank Belknap Long, and Clark Ashton Smith, respectively, not Lovecraft. Maybe you know that, but since this is about Lovecraft I'd have stuck to his creations. Is the unlucky shapeshifting starfish supposed to be Nyarlathotep?

Also, while I love Lovecraft's stuff, I don't feel like this was particularly inspired or provided any real twist. It's pretty much just  which I've seen several times before. It just so happens that the SCP Foundation is there this time, but it didn't really add anything new to the concept. If I'd written this, I'd have made it so the Old Ones didn't actually exist until Lovecraft wrote them, then became more and more powerful as more people read his works, so the Foundation contains them by destroying Lovecraftian fiction that isn't very original either. I'm sure there's some way to do S.C.P. Lovecraft justice, and I don't know what that is, but I know what it isn't.

A very reluctant downvote. I'm sorry.





