I would have wanted to like this. But I am not a fan of crossovers, particularly those that actually try to make one fictional universe actually part of another. In this case, I like Lovecraft and SCP as completely separate entities. To allow Lovecraftian monsters to be real and existing in the SCP universe even if, as noted above, it's simply from Lovecraft himself being a conduit for them to exist, throws me off badly. I tried to like it, but I couldn't. It'd be fine as a tale, but not as a mainline SCP entry.







